<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4945918>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 17. Ronzotherium romani Kretzoi, 1940 from St-Henri/St-André/Les-Milles, near Marseille (late Oligocene, France). – A–B. Maxilla FSL-8547. A. Occlusal view. B. With left P1–M2 in lingual view. – C, E–F. Mandible FSL-8547 from the same individual. C. Occlusal view. E. With left p2–m3 in labial view. F. Right p3–m3 in lingual view. – D. Left i2 NMB-Mar-862, lingual view. – G–H. Left humerus FSL-9523. G. Anterior view. H. Posterior view. – I–J. Right radius FSL-520279+520280. I. Anterior view. J. Posterior view. Scale bar: 2 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4945918/files/figure.png" .

